# YouTube playlist IDs for the "My Watching" section.
#
# HOW TO USE
# ----------
# No API key is required! The ingestor uses YouTube's public Atom/RSS feeds.
#
# The recommended approach is to set YOUTUBE_PLAYLIST_IDS as a GitHub Actions
# repository Variable (repo Settings → Secrets and variables → Variables).
# That way your playlist IDs are never committed to source control, so forks
# of this blog start with a clean slate.
#
# For local development only, you may create the file
#   config/youtube_playlists.txt
# (without the .example extension) and add one playlist ID per line.
# That filename is gitignored, so it will never be committed.
#
# Each playlist returns up to its 15 most-recently-added videos. Add multiple
# playlist IDs (one per line) if you need more history.
#
# HOW TO FIND A PLAYLIST ID
# --------------------------
# Open the playlist on YouTube and copy the "list=" parameter from the URL:
#   https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLAYLIST_ID_HERE
#
# TIP: You can also embed individual YouTube videos in any blog post simply by
# pasting the video URL on its own line. No playlist configuration needed for that.
#
# EXAMPLE ENTRIES (remove the leading # to activate)
# ----------------------------------------------------
